-- Hollande Says Jouyet May Be Assigned ‘Missions,’ Parisien Says
-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 2012-04-28T09:08:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/hollande-says-jouyet-may-be-assigned-missions-parisien-says.html
Jean-Pierre Jouyet, chairman of
 France ’s financial-markets regulator, may be “useful for
missions,” French Socialist Francois Hollande, the leading
presidential candidate, said in an interview with  Le Parisien .  Hollande opposes giving any ministerial jobs to people who
have served under President Nicolas Sarkozy, Le Parisien
reported. Jouyet was Sarkozy’s European Affairs Minister for one
year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fabio Benedetti-Valentini in Paris at 
